content: inicio [GABRIEL LOPEZ MILLAN] Menú principal Menú principal Página de Inicio | Home Docencia | Teaching Investigación | Research Contacto | Contact Presentación Gabriel López Millán is a full time Associate Professor in the Department of Information and Communications Engineering of the University of Murcia. His research interests include network security, SDN networks, IPsec, TLS, IoT security, PKI, AAI, etc. He received his MS and PhD in Computer Science from the University of Murcia in 2006. He has published many papers in JRC-indexed journals and national and international conferences. He is co-author of IETF RFC 9061 and RFC 7499. He has also been involved in several EU research projects related to network security. Cisco CCNA R&S and CCNA Security Instructor since 2005. inicio.txt Última modificación: 2023/07/03 11:19por gabilm@um.es
